// The demo program (inv-K-1 — K.W2 split; N.W1.C mechanism-C resolution).
//
// `demo/` only. Resolves the value.js library through the `@src/*` path and
// `@mkbabb/glass-ui` from its published `dist/` surface (N.W1.C / mechanism-C —
// the `development` source-resolution condition was abrogated constellation-
// wide; glass-ui's `exports` map carries only `{types, import, default}` → all
// `dist/`). Dist-resolution gives a real `.d.ts` trust boundary: glass-ui's
// declaration files are skip-checked (`skipLibCheck`, tsconfig.base.json), so
// vue-tsc reports glass-ui's own internal diagnostics NEVER — the demo
// typecheck sees ZERO foreign errors and needs no error-scoping filter. This is
// why `npm run typecheck` is now the plain direct `vue-tsc -p` gate (the K.W2
// `scripts/check-types.mjs` foreign-error filter was retired at N.W1.C; under
// source-resolution it masked ~164 glass-ui-source diagnostics, which the dist
// trust boundary now eliminates structurally).
//
// glass-ui's published `dist/` imports the value.js core by the bare
// `@mkbabb/value.js` specifier (aurora/color paths, inv-K-2); a package never
// installs itself, so the demo aliases that specifier to value.js's own
// published `dist/value.js` (mirroring the Vite alias in `vite.config.ts`) for
// one consistent published surface.
//
// This is the ONLY value.js program that may see glass-ui; the library program
// (tsconfig.lib.json) never does (inv-K-1 — structurally glass-ui-free).
{
    "extends": "./tsconfig.base.json",
    "compilerOptions": {
        "paths": {
            "@src/*": ["./src/*"],
            "@styles/*": ["./demo/@/styles/*"],
            "@components/*": ["./demo/@/components/*"],
            "@utils/*": ["./demo/@/utils/*"],
            "@lib/*": ["./demo/@/lib/*"],
            "@composables/*": ["./demo/@/composables/*"],
            "@assets/*": ["./assets/*"],
            "vue": ["./node_modules/vue"],
            "@vue/*": ["./node_modules/@vue/*"],
            "@mkbabb/value.js": ["./dist/index.d.ts"]
        }
    },
    // `src/vite-env.d.ts` carries `/// <reference types="vite/client" />`
    // (typing `import.meta.env`, `*.css`, `*?worker`) + the `*.vue`
    // ambient module declaration. The pre-split unified program included it via
    // `src/`; the demo graph needs it for the value.js `src/` modules it pulls in
    // through `@src/*` and for its own Vite-specific imports.
    "include": ["demo/", "src/vite-env.d.ts"]
}
